                                <p><b>Distinguish Colleagues,</b></p>
                                <p>I have the pleasure to welcome you to this maiden edition of the ASFI Annual Virtual Multidisciplinary Conference and Boot Camp. I particularly welcome you to this multidisciplinary scientific engagement in my capacity as the Chair of the Boot Camp Planning Committee, doubling as the pioneer President of the ASFI Members’ General Assembly. In these capacities and counting on my ardent followership of ASFI programs over the last 3 years, I can confidently confess that without continuous research capacity building, Africa’s place in global research reckoning and research-oriented development will remain only a dream. This is the motivation for the Boot Camp</p>
                                <p>The research innovation eco-system necessitates cultivating adaptability and continuous improvement in how relevance, quality and impact of research is imagined and produced. Also, scientific research, technology application and transfer, communication of research results, translation of output for uptake and capturing of impact are foundational to better address the need for meaningful real-world change and to achieve Africa’s developmental goals. However, Africa faces several constraints in relation to the research process, impact, communication and translation of research results to end users. For example, one of the challenges to socio-cultural, economic, political, ecological/environmental and technological advancement in Africa is the limited use of research results for decision-making. Given the dynamic and complex developmental situation Africa faces and the depth and urgency of these challenges, it requires more than just researchers with conventional research skills. Capacity building through anticipatory, active and discerning activities and skills that aid in aligning impact with the desired real world meaningful and transformational change are needed. </p>
                                <p>The ASFI 2023 Virtual Science Boot Camp is a crucible for African scientists at different career levels, fields and expertise who aim to generate desirable change through smart self-training activities. They are researchers who acknowledge context and complexity of problems that require multidisciplinary and collaborative approaches to address, as they promote quality, relevance, impact and meaningful transformation through well-thought-out activities. The end result is to camp and find synergies, share ideas between and across disciplines and discuss issues of key interest in the valorization of research results and products in the developmental process of the African continent. </p>
                                <p>The benefits are idea-sharing, development of ‘soft’ and technical skills, development of strong peer groups, discovering and expansion of networks, building of collaborative projects, sourcing for new opportunities, promoting and celebrating excellence.</p>
